name: Atte: Un Coyotito
description:
Part of my nonformal campaign against the hunting and killing of wildlife, more specific the coyote, which is close to Teotihuacan, I was looking for the best pulque (Ancient Aztec beverage made from the agave or maguey, used only for the elite and higher priest to speak with the gods) of this region and at the end of my trip found this wall, perfect to say something for those without voice.
I didn't notest but in my latest street paintings, I was in pulque::o.
2021, Teotihuacan.
Intercambio Cryptopilejo 2021.
Mucho pulque y animalitos en estas fiestas.
